content.description:
Start at a tree 35 feet from 'A Time for Action'.

 Pitch 1: Climb straight up from the tree, passing short corners and gain the left end of a slanted ledge high up on a cliff.

 Pitch 2: Follow the ledge right and up almost to the end, then continue straight up to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: Start just left of a row of trees in a gulley. Head up 15 feet past the row of trees to a fairly small ledge that slants downward. Climb a small corner, then straight up rock over slight overlaps. Near the top, climb a last overlap past some loose looking rock with a slight corner above. Emerge onto a ledge with a big block. At a lower angle, continue to a cedar tree at the top for a two rope rappel.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description:
35 feet to the left of 'Headstone'. 

 Pitch 1: Scramble up to the highest tree on a lsanting ledge. Climb the orangish corner right of the tree for about 15 feet until you can step left an dgain the leftmost of two parellel cracks. Move up to a horizontal crack, which allows you to gain the rightmost crack. Move right to climb the center of a ceiling at a corner crack. Continue to the same ledge as 'Route 209'.

 Pitch 2: Follow the ledge to the right and up follow a seam and small blocks to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: This is the first wall you come to when approaching from Interstate 80.
